{
  "texts": [
    "However, the distinctions are subtle.",
    "A multimodal census of the neurons of the primate neocortex is necessary to underpin evolutionary changes that augment the capacities of the primate neocortex.Primates exhibit complex brain structures that augment cognitive function.",
    "However, the volume and number of neocortical neurons increased rapidly compared to subcortical structures during the evolutionary expansion of the neocortex [4][5][6][7][8].",
    "While the general principles of cortical development and basic architecture are conserved, studies have shown differences in the cellular composition of the human cortex [9].",
    "These differences include the expansion of superficial cortical layers during mammalian evolution, which may involve rare cell types and novel cellular interactions contributing to the complexity of primate brain function [10]."
  ]
}